    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @lionel218, thanks for opening this issue. InstantSearch.js does not provide event listener per widget. But you can listen to changes of the search state using:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst search = instantsearch(yourConfig);\r\nsearch.start();\r\nsearch.helper.on('change', (state) => {\r\n  // here you can see the values of the search parameters\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you give us the use case, we might be able to give your a more specific answer.",
